<section>
	<h2>Purpose</h2>
	<p>Provide a common design pattern to an exit link and empty the current navigation history when used. There can only be one exit link per page.</p>
	
	<div class="alert alert-warning">
		<p>This design pattern is currently in an experimental state. (Updated: <time datetime="2017-07">July 2017</time>)</p>
	</div>
</section>
<section>
	<h2>Use when</h2>
	<p>When you need to provide a <strong>"quick escape"</strong> or a <strong>"leave this website"</strong> feature for your user because of the sensitivity of your content.</p>
</section>
<section>
	<h2>Do not use when</h2>
	<p>When it is not to provide a quick escape to your user.</p>
	<p>To duplicate a link into bottom overlay, manually create your own bottom overlay with the data inview feature.</p>
</section>
